descript.abstract: The Monongahela National Forest proclamation boundary and purchase units data set has been primarily defined and identified by U.S. Forest Service personnel based on cartographic feature files (CFF) as developed by the Geospatial Technology Center (GSTC) in Salt Lake City. Minor edits have been completed based on legal descriptions identified in Forest survey information. The current direction from the national office is to characterize this layer as the Forest Boundary and not the proclamation boundary.
descript.purpose: This data set is a forest-wide layer that corresponds to National Map Accuracy Standards (NMAS) and serves as the primary GIS administrative boundary layer for the Monongahela National Forest, hereafter characterized as the Forest Boundary.

procstep.procdesc: The Forest Boundary has been generated from USFS cartographic feature files and edited using digital aerial photography/gps points to reflect updates. A portion of the boundary corresponding to a portion of Forest Service Tract 38B was adjusted in October, 2009 based on GPS control points and the survey description for Tract 38B.
